# OFocus — spec discipline

Canonical guidance: [`docs/agent-guide.md`](../../docs/agent-guide.md). Architecture:
[`docs/architecture.md`](../../docs/architecture.md). Specs (the contracts):
`docs/superpowers/specs/`.

Before non-trivial work, read the relevant spec; then hold the code to it.

- **Specs are the contract.** Read the relevant spec **before** changing the change-detection
  engine (`@ofocus/productivity` `changes`), the descriptor registry, or layer/package
  boundaries. If spec, plan, and code disagree, **stop and reconcile** — fix the code to match
  the spec, or update the spec in the same change if the contract is intentionally changing.
  Never silently diverge.
- **Package discipline.** `@ofocus/sdk` stays minimal (only `zod`); network/process/heavy
  things live in `@ofocus/productivity`+ and are fail-open. Deterministic-but-fuzzy logic is
  Layer 2, not the plugin.
- **Single source of truth.** Commands are defined once via `defineCommand`; CLI/MCP/docs
  derive from descriptors — don't hand-maintain parallel lists. Regenerate agent docs
  (`pnpm build`) when the command surface changes.
- **Spec-first tests** (assert spec-derived values, not program output); **changeset** for
  published-package changes; **generated files** (`AGENT_*.md`, `skills/ofocus/SKILL.md`,
  `packages/sdk/docs/*`) are edited via their generator, not by hand.

Full dissonance checklist: [`docs/agent-guide.md`](../../docs/agent-guide.md) §3–4.
